        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cron): configurable minimum interval guardrail for recurring jobs",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdds an opt-in `cron.minInterval` setting that enforces a **minimum interval between fires for recurring cron jobs**. \r\nFor hosted OpenClaw, we want to define guardrails for the users, and very frequent cron is wasteful/costly. So we want it to fail fast.\r\nWith two layers driven by the one config value:\r\n\r\n1. **Creation-time rejection (UX layer):** creating or editing an `every`/`cron` job whose schedule falls below the floor fails with a clear error, so the agent or CLI caller immediately picks a saner cadence. For `cron` expressions this checks the smallest gap across sampled upcoming fires — documented as best-effort feedback, since bounded sampling cannot prove an expression's true minimum gap.\r\n2. **Fire-time floor (enforcement layer):** the scheduler paces every re-arm so consecutive fires of a recurring job stay at least `minInterval` apart (start-to-start, launchd `ThrottleInterval`-style). This is the contract the docs promise: it covers jobs created before the limit was configured, cron expressions whose tight gaps escape sampling, restarts, and update re-arms. Deferred fires log a warning naming the job.\r\n\r\nMotivation: hosted/operator deployments need a real resource limit on cron frequency, not just a creation-side suggestion — while still blocking bad schedules up front so users learn the limit at the moment they can act on it. Mirrors the `cron.maxConcurrentRuns` operator-guardrail pattern.\r\n\r\n## What changed\r\n\r\n- **Config surface**: `cron.minInterval` (`CronConfig` type, zod schema + duration validation, help text, label, docs). Duration string (`30s`, `5m`, `1h`) or milliseconds; default `0`/unset = no limit.\r\n- **Resolver**: `resolveCronMinIntervalMs()` in `src/config/cron-limits.ts`.\r\n- **Creation validation**: `assertScheduleMeetsMinInterval()` in the cron service, from `createJob` and schedule-changing `update`s. Maps to `INVALID_REQUEST` in the gateway handler; the cron tool description tells agents to increase the interval instead of retrying.\r\n- **Fire-time floor**: `minIntervalFloorAtMs()` (`src/cron/service/jobs.ts`) applied at every `nextRunAtMs` writer:\r\n  - completion + error-backoff re-arm (`applyJobResult`, timer.ts) with a deferral warning;\r\n  - `update()` re-arm (ops.ts) — a bare `{enabled: true}` update can no longer reset a deferred fire;\r\n  - maintenance/repair recompute (`recomputeJobNextRunAtMs`) so `repairFutureCronNextRunAtMs` cannot undo deferrals (floored values also skip repair, avoiding per-tick rework);\r\n  - restart paths: startup missed-slot catch-up and pending-backoff deferral respect the floor.\r\n- **Scope decisions**: one-shot `at` jobs exempt; manual/forced runs (`preserveSchedule`) never shift the schedule and are not floored; transient-failure retries follow `cron.retry`; a 2s dispatch slack keeps schedules whose cadence exactly equals the floor on their natural slots (no drift, no warning spam); floor `0`/unset preserves shipped behavior exactly.\r\n\r\n## Config example\r\n\r\n```json5\r\n{\r\n  cron: {\r\n    minInterval: \"5m\", // recurring jobs neither validate nor fire more often than every 5 minutes\r\n  },\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCreation error shape: `cron schedule fires every 30s, below the minimum interval of 5m`.\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\nRun locally (clean):\r\n\r\n- `oxfmt --check` + `oxlint` on touched files — clean\r\n- `tsgo -p tsconfig.core.json` and `-p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json` — clean for touched code (two pre-existing errors in `src/config/io.ts`/`src/secrets/config-io.ts` come from the branch base and are already fixed on `main`; rebase resolves)\r\n- Full cron subsystem: `src/cron` — 101 test files, 1002 tests, all green\r\n- New behavior tests `src/cron/service.min-interval-floor.test.ts`: pre-existing every/cron jobs paced + warned; error-path pacing; no-floor regression guard; at-floor schedule keeps natural cadence under dispatch jitter; force runs preserve the schedule; enable-toggle update keeps the floor; startup catch-up does not replay a missed slot inside the floor window\r\n- Existing suites re-run green: `jobs.min-interval`, `service.jobs`, `jobs.apply-patch`, `ops`, `ops.regression`, `timer`, `timer.regression`, `armtimer-tight-loop`, `every-jobs-fire`, issue regressions 13992/17852/66019, `cron-limits`, `zod-schema.cron-min-interval`, `schema.help.quality`\r\n\r\nMulti-agent adversarial review of the floor change ran pre-push; confirmed findings (force-run schedule shift, enable-toggle bypass, restart catch-up/backoff bypasses, at-floor jitter drift, maintenance repair undoing deferrals) are all fixed and regression-tested above.\r\n",
        "branch": "ak/cron-min-interval",
